    <p>U.S. Supreme Court</p>
    <h1>PENNSYLVANIA CO, EX PARTE, <a href="./us137-0457.xml#p457">137 U.S. 457</a> (1890)</h1>
    <p><a href="./us137-0457.xml#p457">137 U.S. 457</a></p>
    <p>Ex parte PENNSYLVANIA CO.</p>
    <p>December 8, 1890.</p>
    <p>Page <a href="./us137-0457.xml#p457">137 U.S. 457</a>, 458</p>
    <p>Danl. Davenport and William H. O'Hara, for petitioner.</p>
    <p>Lewis E. Stanton, for respondent.</p>
    <p>BRADLEY, J.</p>
    <p>This case in all material respects is identical with the case of Ex parte Pennsylvania Co., ante, 141, (just decided,) and the same conclusion is reached as in that case. The petition for mandamus is denied.</p>
